ABA stands for Applied Behavior Analysis and is a therapy that is based on analyzing and studying behavior and It has been used to help children on the autism spectrum gain skills and live healthier lives since the ABA therapy takes into account how behavior works, how it’s affected by the environment we’re in, and how learning takes The goal of ABA therapy is to increase helpful behaviors and decrease harmful behaviors while creating a personalized treatment program that meets the unique needs of each ABA Therapy helps to: Increase language and communication skills Improve attention, focus, social skills, memory, and academics Promote independence and Start your child on the path to progress today! Our Process: Introductory Call On your initial call, we’ll listen to your concerns and provide information on autism, ABA therapy, and what’s needed to begin the Insurance and Diagnostic Evaluation After verifying insurance coverage, we’ll assist your family in scheduling a diagnostic If you already have a diagnostic report, we’ll submit it to insurance for Initial Assessment After the report is approved by insurance, a qualified BCBA (Board Certified Behavior Analyst) will perform a detailed assessment, which includes analyzing your child’s skills, listening to your concerns, and determining how many hours of therapy your child needs per This assessment is then sent to insurance for Treatment Plan Once approved, we create a treatment plan, which includes specific goals and is customized to your child’s skills, needs, preferences, and Therapy Begins We match up an RBT (Registered Behavior Technician) to provide ABA therapy at the location and schedule that works for your Some of the areas your child may be working on include communication, social skills, , play and leisure, motor skills, and academic Each skill is broken down into small, concrete steps, making mastery Progress Monitoring & Parent Training Your child’s progress is measured to make sure that he is moving towards his goals on a regular We meet with your family weekly to review progress and plan new How We Maintain Our Level of Personal Connection A dedicated case manager is your point of contact and always keeps in touch to make sure you’re satisfied with your team and feel supported throughout every stage of the Steady Supervision Our Clinical Director oversees and leads our team of BCBA’s in each state, with a BCBA shadowing your RBT regularly to ensure the treatment plan is being carried out Parent Support To ensure ABA therapy carries over into home life, you’ll meet with your child’s BCBA once a week to help feel confident in techniques, address new challenges, answer questions and get
